{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"format"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"format"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!) -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE6formatADSSSgSPys4Int8VGSg_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib8DateTimeC","title":"format(format:)"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"format","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"format","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!) -> "},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The format strings understood by this function are a subset of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" format language as specified by C99.  The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"D"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"U","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"W"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conversions are not supported, nor is the "},{"code":"E","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifier.  The GNU","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"extensions "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"k"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"l"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"s"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"P","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" are supported, however, as are the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-"},{"text":" modifiers. The Python extension ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"f"},{"text":" is also supported.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In contrast to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":", this function always produces a UTF-8"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"string, regardless of the current locale.  Note that the rendering of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"many formats is locale-dependent and may not match the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"output exactly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following format specifiers are supported:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"a"},{"text":": the abbreviated weekday name according to the current locale","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"A"},{"type":"text","text":": the full weekday name according to the current locale"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"},{"text":": the abbreviated month name according to the current locale","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"B","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the full month name according to the current locale"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"c","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date and time representation for the current locale"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"type":"text","text":": the century number (year\/100) as a 2-digit integer (00-99)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"d"},{"type":"text","text":": the day of the month as a decimal number (range 01 to 31)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/e-3m6a4"},{"type":"text","text":": the day of the month as a decimal number (range 1 to 31);"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"F"},{"type":"text","text":": equivalent to "},{"code":"Y-","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"m-","type":"text"},{"code":"d","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (the ISO 8601 date format)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"g","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the last two digits of the ISO 8601 week-based year as a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"decimal number (00-99). This works well with "},{"code":"V","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G"},{"text":": the ISO 8601 week-based year as a decimal number. This works","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"well with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"h"},{"text":": equivalent to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour as a decimal number using a 24-hour clock (range 00 to 23)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"I"},{"text":": the hour as a decimal number using a 12-hour clock (range 01 to 12)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"j","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the day of the year as a decimal number (range 001 to 366)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"k"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour (24-hour clock) as a decimal number (range 0 to 23);"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"l","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the hour (12-hour clock) as a decimal number (range 1 to 12);","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"m"},{"text":": the month as a decimal number (range 01 to 12)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"M"},{"text":": the minute as a decimal number (range 00 to 59)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"f"},{"text":": the microsecond as a decimal number (range 000000 to 999999)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"p"},{"text":": either ‘AM’ or ‘PM’ according to the given time value, or the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"corresponding  strings for the current locale.  Noon is treated as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"‘PM’ and midnight as ‘AM’. Use of this format specifier is discouraged, as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"P","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": like "},{"code":"p","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" but lowercase: ‘am’ or ‘pm’ or a corresponding string for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the current locale. Use of this format specifier is discouraged, as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"r"},{"type":"text","text":": the time in a.m. or p.m. notation. Use of this format specifier is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"discouraged, as many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or ","type":"text"},{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"R","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time in 24-hour notation (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H:"},{"type":"text","text":"M``)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"s","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the number of seconds since the Epoch, that is, since 1970-01-01"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"00:00:00 UTC"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"S","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the second as a decimal number (range 00 to 60)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"t"},{"text":": a tab character","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"T","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the time in 24-hour notation with seconds ("},{"code":"H:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"M:","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"S"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the ISO 8601 standard day of the week as a decimal, range 1 to 7,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Monday being 1. This works well with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"type":"text","text":": the ISO 8601 standard week number of the current year as a decimal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"number, range 01 to 53, where week 1 is the first week that has at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"least 4 days in the new year. See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This works well with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"w"},{"text":": the day of the week as a decimal, range 0 to 6, Sunday being 0.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is not the ISO 8601 standard format — use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date representation for the current locale without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the time"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred time representation for the current locale without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the date","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"y","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the year as a decimal number without the century","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Y","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the year as a decimal number including the century","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"z"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+hhmm"},{"text":")","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":":z"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+hh:mm"},{"text":").","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is a gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" extension. Since: 2.38"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"::z","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC ("},{"code":"+hh:mm:ss","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"). This is a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"gnulib "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" extension. Since: 2.38","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":":::z"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC, with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":":"},{"text":" to necessary","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"precision (e.g., "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-04"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+05:30"},{"text":"). This is a gnulib ","type":"text"},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" extension. Since: 2.38","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Z","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone or name or abbreviation"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"``````: a literal ```` character","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some conversion specifications can be modified by preceding the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conversion specifier by one or more modifier characters."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following modifiers are supported for many of the numeric","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"conversions:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"O","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Use alternative numeric symbols, if the current locale supports those.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_"},{"text":": Pad a numeric result with spaces. This overrides the default padding","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for the specifier."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Do not pad a numeric result. This overrides the default padding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the specifier."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Pad a numeric result with zeros. This overrides the default padding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the specifier."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following modifiers are supported for many of the alphabetic conversions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"^","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Use upper case if possible. This is a gnulib ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" extension."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Since: 2.80"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#"},{"type":"text","text":": Use opposite case if possible. This is a gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"extension. Since: 2.80","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Additionally, when "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"O"},{"type":"text","text":" is used with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"B"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"h"},{"type":"text","text":", it produces the alternative"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"form of a month name. The alternative form should be used when the month","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"name is used without a day number (e.g., standalone). It is required in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"some languages (Baltic, Slavic, Greek, and more) due to their grammatical"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"rules. For other languages there is no difference. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OB"},{"type":"text","text":" is a GNU and BSD"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extension expected to be added to the future POSIX specification,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"Ob","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Oh"},{"type":"text","text":" are GNU "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extensions. Since: 2.56"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since GLib 2.80, when ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"E"},{"type":"text","text":" is used with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"y"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"Y","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the date is formatted using an alternate era representation specific to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"locale. This is typically used for the Thai solar calendar or Japanese era"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"names, for example."}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Ec","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date and time representation for the current locale,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"using the alternate era representation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"EC","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the name of the era","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Ex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date representation for the current locale without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the time, using the alternate era representation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"EX","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred time representation for the current locale without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the date, using the alternate era representation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ey"},{"text":": the year since the beginning of the era denoted by the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EC"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specifier","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"co